00003 /* RSC IDENTIFIER: Coordinate Conversion Service

00005  * ABSTRACT
00006  *
00007  *    This component is the coordinate conversion service for the MSPCCS
00008  *    application.  It provides an external input interface that supports the
00009  *    MSPCCS GUI (Java) and the MSPCCS file processing
00010  *    component.
00011  *
00012  *    This component depends on the DT&CC modules:  DATUM, ELLIPSOID,
00013  *    GEOCENTRIC, GEOREF, MERCATOR, TRANSVERSE MERCATOR, UTM, MGRS, USNG, POLAR
00014  *    STEREOGRAPHIC, UPS, LAMBERT_1, LAMBERT_2, ALBERS, AZIMUTHAL EQUIDISTANT, BONNE,
00015  *    BRITISH NATIONAL GRID,  CASSINI, CYLINDRICAL EQUAL AREA,ECKERT4, ECKERT6,

00017  *    NEYS, NEW ZEALAND MAP GRID, OBLIQUE MERCATOR, ORTHOGRAPHIC, POLYCONIC,
00018  *    SINUSOIDAL, STEREOGRAPHIC, TRANSVERSE CYLINDRICAL EQUAL AREA, and VAN DER GRINTEN.
00019  *
00020  *
00021  * ERROR HANDLING
00022  *
00023  *    This component checks for error codes returned by the DT&CC modules.
00024  *    If an error code is returned, it is combined with the current
00025  *    error code using the bitwise or.  This combining allows multiple error
00026  *    codes to be returned. The possible error codes are listed below.
00027  *
00028  *
00029  * REUSE NOTES
00030  *
00031  *    Coordinate Conversion Service is intended for reuse by other applications that require
00032  *    coordinate conversions between multiple coordinate systems and/or datum
00033  *    transformations between multiple datums.
00034  *
00035  *
00036  * REFERENCES
00037  *
00038  *    Further information on Coordinate Conversion Service can be found in the Coordinate
00039  *    Conversion Service Reuse Manual.

02229                 break;
02230               case HeightType::noHeight:
02231                 _wgs84Geodetic->setHeight( 0.0 );
02232                 break;
02233               case HeightType::ellipsoidHeight:
02234               default:
02235                 break;
02236             }
02237 
02238             /* check source datum validity */
02239             long sourceValid = 0;
02240 
02241             datumLibraryImplementation->validDatum( source->datumIndex, _wgs84Geodetic->longitude(), _wgs84Geodetic->latitude(), &sourceValid );
02242             if( !sourceValid )
02243             {
02244               strcat( sourceWarningMessage, MSP::CCS::WarningMessages::datum );
02245             }
02246           }
02247           else
02248           { /* Copy coordinate tuple */
02249             _wgs84Geodetic = new GeodeticCoordinates( *_convertedGeodetic );
02250             if( input_height_type == HeightType::noHeight )
02251               _wgs84Geodetic->setHeight( 0.0 );
02252           }
02253 
02254           if(input_height_type != output_height_type)
02255           {
02256             double tempHeight;
02257 
02258             /* Convert the source height value to an ellipsoid height value */
02259             switch(input_height_type)
02260             {
02261               case HeightType::EGM96FifteenMinBilinear:
02262                 geoidLibrary->convertEGM96FifteenMinBilinearGeoidToEllipsoidHeight( _wgs84Geodetic->longitude(), _wgs84Geodetic->latitude(),
02263                                                   _wgs84Geodetic->height(), &tempHeight);
02264                 break;
02265               case HeightType::EGM96VariableNaturalSpline:
02266                 geoidLibrary->convertEGM96VariableNaturalSplineToEllipsoidHeight( _wgs84Geodetic->longitude(), _wgs84Geodetic->latitude(),
02267                                                             _wgs84Geodetic->height(), &tempHeight );
02268                 break;
02269               case HeightType::EGM84TenDegBilinear:
02270                 geoidLibrary->convertEGM84TenDegBilinearToEllipsoidHeight( _wgs84Geodetic->longitude(), _wgs84Geodetic->latitude(),
02271                                                              _wgs84Geodetic->height(), &tempHeight );
02272                 break;
02273               case HeightType::EGM84TenDegNaturalSpline:
02274                 geoidLibrary->convertEGM84TenDegNaturalSplineToEllipsoidHeight( _wgs84Geodetic->longitude(), _wgs84Geodetic->latitude(),
02275                                                              _wgs84Geodetic->height(), &tempHeight );
02276                 break;
02277               case HeightType::ellipsoidHeight:
02278               default:
02279                 tempHeight = _wgs84Geodetic->height();
02280                 break;
02281             }
02282 
02283             double correctedHeight;
02284 
02285             /* Convert the ellipsoid height value to the target height value */
02286             switch(output_height_type)
02287             {
02288               case HeightType::EGM96FifteenMinBilinear:
02289                 geoidLibrary->convertEllipsoidToEGM96FifteenMinBilinearGeoidHeight( _wgs84Geodetic->longitude(), _wgs84Geodetic->latitude(),
02290                                                             tempHeight, &correctedHeight );
02291                 break;
02292               case HeightType::EGM96VariableNaturalSpline:
02293                 geoidLibrary->convertEllipsoidToEGM96VariableNaturalSplineHeight( _wgs84Geodetic->longitude(), _wgs84Geodetic->latitude(),
02294                                                             tempHeight, &correctedHeight );
02295                 break;
02296               case HeightType::EGM84TenDegBilinear:
02297                 geoidLibrary->convertEllipsoidToEGM84TenDegBilinearHeight( _wgs84Geodetic->longitude(), _wgs84Geodetic->latitude(),
02298                                                              tempHeight, &correctedHeight );
02299                 break;
02300               case HeightType::EGM84TenDegNaturalSpline:
02301                 geoidLibrary->convertEllipsoidToEGM84TenDegNaturalSplineHeight( _wgs84Geodetic->longitude(), _wgs84Geodetic->latitude(),
02302                                                              tempHeight, &correctedHeight );
02303                 break;
02304               case HeightType::ellipsoidHeight:
02305               default:
02306                 correctedHeight = tempHeight;
02307                 break;
02308             }
02309 
02310             /* Set the target height */
02311             _wgs84Geodetic->setHeight( correctedHeight );
02312           }
02313 
02314           if (target->datumIndex != WGS84_datum_index)
02315           {
02316             _shiftedGeodetic = datumLibraryImplementation->geodeticShiftFromWGS84( _wgs84Geodetic, target->datumIndex );
02317 
02318             switch(output_height_type)
02319             {
02320               case HeightType::EGM96FifteenMinBilinear:
02321               case HeightType::EGM96VariableNaturalSpline:
02322               case HeightType::EGM84TenDegBilinear:
02323               case HeightType::EGM84TenDegNaturalSpline:
02324                 _shiftedGeodetic->setHeight( _wgs84Geodetic->height() );
02325                 break;
02326               case HeightType::noHeight:
02327                 _shiftedGeodetic->setHeight( 0.0 );
02328                 break;
02329               case HeightType::ellipsoidHeight:
02330               default:
02331                 break;
02332             }
02333 
02334             /* check target datum validity */
02335             long targetValid = 0;
02336 
02337             datumLibraryImplementation->validDatum( target->datumIndex, _wgs84Geodetic->longitude(), _wgs84Geodetic->latitude(),
02338                                                    &targetValid );
02339             if( !targetValid )
02340             {
02341               strcat( targetWarningMessage, MSP::CCS::WarningMessages::datum );
02342             }
02343           }
02344           else
02345           { /* Copy coordinate tuple */
02346             _shiftedGeodetic = new GeodeticCoordinates( *_wgs84Geodetic );
02347             if( output_height_type == HeightType::noHeight )
02348               _shiftedGeodetic->setHeight( 0.0 );
02349           }
02350         }
02351 
02352       /* calculate conversion errors */
02353       if( strlen( sourceWarningMessage ) > 0 || strlen( targetWarningMessage ) > 0 )
02354         targetAccuracy.set(-1.0, -1.0, -1.0);
02355       else
02356       {
02357         Accuracy* _targetAccuracy = datumLibraryImplementation->datumShiftError( source->datumIndex, target->datumIndex,
02358                                         _wgs84Geodetic->longitude(), _wgs84Geodetic->latitude(), sourceAccuracy );
02359 
02360         targetAccuracy.set( _targetAccuracy->circularError90(), _targetAccuracy->linearError90(), _targetAccuracy->sphericalError90() );
02361 
02362         delete _targetAccuracy;
02363       }
02364 
02365       /*************************************************************/
02366       /* Second coordinate conversion stage, convert from Geodetic */
02367       /*************************************************************/
02368 
02369       convertGeodeticToTarget( targetDirection, _shiftedGeodetic, targetCoordinates, targetWarningMessage );
02370 
02371       // Format and set the warning message in the target coordinates
02372       char warningMessage[500] = "";
02373       bool warning = false;
02374       if( strlen( sourceWarningMessage ) > 0 )
02375       {
02376         strcpy( warningMessage, "Input " );
02377         strcat( warningMessage, Coordinate_System_Table[source->coordinateType].Name );
02378         strcat( warningMessage, ": \n" );
02379         strcat( warningMessage, sourceWarningMessage );
02380         warning = true;
02381       }
02382     
02383       if( strlen( targetWarningMessage ) > 0 )
02384       {
02385         if( strlen( warningMessage ) > 0 )
02386           strcat( warningMessage, "\nOutput " );
02387         else
02388           strcpy( warningMessage, "Output " );
02389 
02390         strcat( warningMessage, Coordinate_System_Table[target->coordinateType].Name );
02391         strcat( warningMessage, ": \n" );
02392         strcat( warningMessage, targetWarningMessage );
02393         warning = true;
02394       }
02395       
02396       if( warning )
02397       {
02398         warningMessage[strlen( warningMessage )] = '\0';
02399         targetCoordinates.setWarningMessage(warningMessage);
02400       }
02401     } /* if (!special) */
02402   }
02403   catch(CoordinateConversionException e)
02404   {
02405     targetAccuracy.set(-1.0, -1.0, -1.0);
02406 
02407     if( !mutex_error )
02408       mutex_error = Threads_Unlock_Mutex( mutex );
02409     if( !mutex_error )
02410       Threads_Destroy_Mutex( mutex );
02411 
02412     throw CoordinateConversionException(e.getMessage());        
02413   }
02414 
02415   delete _convertedGeodetic;
02416   delete _shiftedGeodetic;
02417   delete _wgs84Geodetic;
02418 
02419   if( !mutex_error )
02420     mutex_error = Threads_Unlock_Mutex( mutex );
02421   if( !mutex_error )
02422     Threads_Destroy_Mutex( mutex );
02423 }
